ind when they consider any possible wizard enhancements.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Channeler</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:39:33 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: OK</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Regarding Lure Spells for lower levels: Gullerback is lower than level 50, as is the EXG in Solusek.  Further, there are some monsters who just have high resistances, and a Lure might be handy then.  The fact is, even if they weren't as useful as they are post 50, it makes sense to have them earlier (just like it does draught spells) just from a concept point.<br>
